 TDn2K is a small niche research practice and data    warehouse driven by transforming data into knowledge for our    clients. We serve a community of leading companies who utilize our    research and services to improve their business practices.  Our    team-oriented, relaxed, collaborative culture which is more about    successful delivery as a team, rather than about competition and    bureaucracy between the team members.    We are looking for a hands-on, self-starter full stack    web application developer who can improve and expand the existing    MEAN Stack applications.    Requirements:   BS in Computer Sciences or similar fields with 2-4      years or hands on development experience or equivalent    Hands on MEAN (MongoDB, Express, AngularJS and NodeJS      experience) or in similar technologies including UI, business      logic and backend development  AngularJS or other UI framework experience is of      particular importance  Hands on experience building UIs using HTML,      JavaScript, CSS  Skilled at troubleshooting production issues in MEAN      stack application  Experienced at writing SQL queries in relational      databases like MySQL or MS SQL and non-relational databases like  MongoDB  Understand algorithms, data structures and software  design  Strong willingness to learn and apply new skills and  technologies  Must be comfortable interacting with persons of      diverse backgrounds  Sense of (and appreciation of) humor     Nice to have skills and experience:   Excitement about implementing automated unit  testing  Experience with WordPress, .NET, Java or similar  technologies  AWS or other cloud deployment experience  Jenkins, Docker, Chef or similar continuous      integration scripting skills  eCommerce experience  Highcharts.js, D3.js and similar libraries are strong  plus  Version control experience (Git, Subversion,  etc.)  Scrum or other Agile experience  Experience operating in small development teams where      you wear many hats  Experience with design patterns  Willingness to try new approaches to solve  problems     Responsibilities:   Collaborating in design including suggesting new      approaches in positives ways,  Implementing development,   Saving code in version control system,  Building automated unit tests,  Documentation of design decisions, architecture and      operations needs,   Developing automation to deploy through Jenkins,    Managing, troubleshooting and resolving  bugs  Helping other team members as needed and  able  Learning new skills and having fun in relaxed  culture   &amp;nbsp &amp;nbsp  Your team:  Our staff has as a committed work ethic and loves to    crunch numbers and has fun together; they chat, joke &amp; tell    stories. Relationships are strong. Your co-workers will probably ask    you on your first day what your favorite music group, favorite    beer/wine, and/or if you have pets   their names, you know, the    important things in life!     Hours:   This position is a salaried, full-time position.    Project/implementation deadlines will dictate your schedule to a    large extent. It may take long hours and/or weekends to meet some    deadlines. As we mentioned up front, you need to be passionate about    what you do.     About us:  We are a small niche research practice and data house    driven by transforming data into knowledge for our clients. We serve    a community of leading companies who utilize our research and    services to improve their business practices.     Our approach:  We approach our clients  businesses from an integrated    perspective; their success means our success. And, we re passionate    about our business and our clients  businesses   really passionate.    We keep our clients for a long time and a part of the reason is    because we learn the multiple aspects of their business from the    inside out, as if it were our own. We are proud of the fact that we    move the needle, building best practices and loyalty for our    clients, but we know we couldn t do that if we didn t get in there    and make sure our clients truly  get  it. We strive for zero-defect    in all our work as data integrity, security and quality are the    cornerstones of our business.     Your working environment:  Fun and casual. Your team is hard working and focused    upon doing great work for the client   but we never forget to have    fun in the process. It will be fast paced and deadline filled and we    all enjoy coming to work... most days.     Our values:   TDn2K is a small group of professionals who consider    each other family. Our leaders get a rush out of seeing our    employees blossom and grow. We strive to be and work with companies    that are socially responsible. We all contribute to our communities    from working with Share our Strength to Habitat for Humanity and we    all have great stories to tell about our experiences.
]

