The Met Museum is seeking a talented, flexible and focused Lead  Quality Assurance Specialist to join our software development team.  She/He is responsible for leading managing and coordinating all QA  tasks across mobile apps, and websites, and management of the overall  QA process and workflow. Working with each product or project team,  their goal is to ensure the team delivers the highest level of quality  in our deliverables through continuous testing of  functionality/usability and review of visual elements, proofreading,  and validation during critical stages of development. This position  shares responsibility for building and maintaining internal lines of  communication, and creating/refining departmental process. This is a highly rewarding role, and is part of a dynamic,  forward-thinking and ambitious software development team responsible  for connecting the Museum s incredible art and scholarship with  audiences from around the world, both online and on-site.   PRIMARY RESPONSIBILIES &amp; DUTIES:  Test functionality and review visual elements of small- and    large-scale interactive deliverables Document and    facilitate communication and troubleshooting of issues, bugs,  changes Validate and close-out all issues prior to client  delivery Collaborate with other QA staff to accomplish all    daily QA tasks on-time with a high level of quality Develop    process to ensure the highest level of quality assurance  possible Investigate procedures, workflows, and software to    keep our processes up to date Lead and mentor QA team    members and share expertise Conduct daily touch base    meetings with QA and software leads Work closely with    partners and producers on company process Assist in the    development of on-going training programs for the QA Team Provide department specific orientation and training for new  hires Maintain open communication with internal teams Assist with internal project kickoffs and requirements/specs  gathering Plan and document the testing effort via test plans    and test cases for larger-scale projects Creation and    maintenance of automated scripts Interface with and manage    3rd party QA providers Other duties as assigned.&amp;nbsp     REQUIREMENTS &amp; QUALIFICATIONS:   Experience and Skills:  3+ years Quality Assurance or equivalent experience QA framework knowledge (cf Selenium, TestComplete) Excellent verbal and written communication skills Experience working in an Agile environment Demonstrated    mentoring and management skills Strong positive attitude    and a demonstrated ability to accomplish complicated projects with  confidence Strong commitment to department and company  goals Demonstrated ability to creatively and proactively    solve problems Ability to learn quickly and work  efficiently Must be a team player with the ability to manage    multiple tasks in a deadline driven environment   Demonstrated leadership, presentation, and resource allocation  skills Raw enthusiasm and a strong work ethic Highly    organized with a keen attention to detail Proven written    and verbal communication skills College degree or    equivalent experience required   Creativity, flexibility, sense of humor      Benefits:  Strong work/life balance 10+ paid holiday days  annually 27 days paid annual leave 401K with option    for employer matching plan Health and Dental Insurance Early access to exhibitions, galleries, and curatorial  talks A fantastic work environment!       &amp;nbsp
]
